5194/* Generate insns to trap with code TCODE if OP1 and OP2 satisfy condition
5195 CODE. Return 0 on failure. */
5196
5197rtx_insn *
5198gen_cond_trap (enum rtx_code code, rtx op1, rtx op2, rtx tcode)
5199{
5200 machine_mode mode = GET_MODE (op1);
5201 enum insn_code icode;
5202 rtx_insn *insn;
5203 rtx trap_rtx;
5204
5205 if (mode == VOIDmode)
5206 return 0;
5207
5208 icode = optab_handler (ctrap_optab, mode);
5209 if (icode == CODE_FOR_nothing)
5210 return 0;
5211
5212 /* Some targets only accept a zero trap code. */
5213 if (!insn_operand_matches (icode, 3, tcode))
5214 return 0;
5215
5216 do_pending_stack_adjust ();
5217 start_sequence ();
5218 prepare_cmp_insn (op1, op2, code, NULL_RTX, false, OPTAB_DIRECT,
5219 &trap_rtx, &mode);
5220 if (!trap_rtx)
5221 insn = NULL;
5222 else
5223 insn = GEN_FCN (icode) (trap_rtx, XEXP (trap_rtx, 0), XEXP (trap_rtx, 1),
5224 tcode);
5225
5226 /* If that failed, then give up. */
5227 if (insn == 0)
5228 {
5229 end_sequence ();
5230 return 0;
5231 }
5232
5233 emit_insn (insn);
5234 insn = get_insns ();
5235 end_sequence ();
5236 return insn;
5237}
5238
5239/* Return rtx code for TCODE. Use UNSIGNEDP to select signed
5240 or unsigned operation code. */
5241
5242enum rtx_code
5243get_rtx_code (enum tree_code tcode, bool unsignedp)
5244{
5245 enum rtx_code code;
5246 switch (tcode)
5247 {
5248 case EQ_EXPR:
5249 code = EQ;
5250 break;
5251 case NE_EXPR:
5252 code = NE;
5253 break;
5254 case LT_EXPR:
5255 code = unsignedp ? LTU : LT;
5256 break;
5257 case LE_EXPR:
5258 code = unsignedp ? LEU : LE;
5259 break;
5260 case GT_EXPR:
5261 code = unsignedp ? GTU : GT;
5262 break;
5263 case GE_EXPR:
5264 code = unsignedp ? GEU : GE;
5265 break;
5266
5267 case UNORDERED_EXPR:
5268 code = UNORDERED;
5269 break;
5270 case ORDERED_EXPR:
5271 code = ORDERED;
5272 break;
5273 case UNLT_EXPR:
5274 code = UNLT;
5275 break;
5276 case UNLE_EXPR:
5277 code = UNLE;
5278 break;
5279 case UNGT_EXPR:
5280 code = UNGT;
5281 break;
5282 case UNGE_EXPR:
5283 code = UNGE;
5284 break;
5285 case UNEQ_EXPR:
5286 code = UNEQ;
5287 break;
5288 case LTGT_EXPR:
5289 code = LTGT;
5290 break;
5291
5292 case BIT_AND_EXPR:
5293 code = AND;
5294 break;
5295
5296 case BIT_IOR_EXPR:
5297 code = IOR;
5298 break;
5299
5300 default:
5301 gcc_unreachable ();
5302 }
5303 return code;
5304}
5305
5306/* Return a comparison rtx of mode CMP_MODE for COND. Use UNSIGNEDP to
5307 select signed or unsigned operators. OPNO holds the index of the
5308 first comparison operand for insn ICODE. Do not generate the
5309 compare instruction itself. */
5310
5311static rtx
5312vector_compare_rtx (machine_mode cmp_mode, enum tree_code tcode,
5313 tree t_op0, tree t_op1, bool unsignedp,
5314 enum insn_code icode, unsigned int opno)
5315{
5316 struct expand_operand ops[2];
5317 rtx rtx_op0, rtx_op1;
5318 machine_mode m0, m1;
5319 enum rtx_code rcode = get_rtx_code (tcode, unsignedp);
5320
5321 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE_CLASS (tcode) == tcc_comparison);
5322
5323 /* Expand operands. For vector types with scalar modes, e.g. where int64x1_t
5324 has mode DImode, this can produce a constant RTX of mode VOIDmode; in such
5325 cases, use the original mode. */
5326 rtx_op0 = expand_expr (t_op0, NULL_RTX, TYPE_MODE (TREE_TYPE (t_op0)),
5327 EXPAND_STACK_PARM);
5328 m0 = GET_MODE (rtx_op0);
5329 if (m0 == VOIDmode)
5330 m0 = TYPE_MODE (TREE_TYPE (t_op0));
5331
5332 rtx_op1 = expand_expr (t_op1, NULL_RTX, TYPE_MODE (TREE_TYPE (t_op1)),
5333 EXPAND_STACK_PARM);
5334 m1 = GET_MODE (rtx_op1);
5335 if (m1 == VOIDmode)
5336 m1 = TYPE_MODE (TREE_TYPE (t_op1));
5337
5338 create_input_operand (&ops[0], rtx_op0, m0);
5339 create_input_operand (&ops[1], rtx_op1, m1);
5340 if (!maybe_legitimize_operands (icode, opno, 2, ops))
5341 gcc_unreachable ();
5342 return gen_rtx_fmt_ee (rcode, cmp_mode, ops[0].value, ops[1].value);
5343}
5344
5345/* Checks if vec_perm mask SEL is a constant equivalent to a shift of the first
5346 vec_perm operand, assuming the second operand is a constant vector of zeroes.
5347 Return the shift distance in bits if so, or NULL_RTX if the vec_perm is not a
5348 shift. */
5349static rtx
5350shift_amt_for_vec_perm_mask (rtx sel)
5351{
5352 unsigned int i, first, nelt = GET_MODE_NUNITS (GET_MODE (sel));
5353 unsigned int bitsize = GET_MODE_UNIT_BITSIZE (GET_MODE (sel));
5354
5355 if (GET_CODE (sel) != CONST_VECTOR)
5356 return NULL_RTX;
5357
5358 first = INTVAL (CONST_VECTOR_ELT (sel, 0));
5359 if (first >= nelt)
5360 return NULL_RTX;
5361 for (i = 1; i < nelt; i++)
5362 {
5363 int idx = INTVAL (CONST_VECTOR_ELT (sel, i));
5364 unsigned int expected = i + first;
5365 /* Indices into the second vector are all equivalent. */
5366 if (idx < 0 || (MIN (nelt, (unsigned) idx) != MIN (nelt, expected)))
5367 return NULL_RTX;
5368 }
5369
5370 return GEN_INT (first * bitsize);
5371}
5372
5373/* A subroutine of expand_vec_perm for expanding one vec_perm insn. */
5374
5375static rtx
5376expand_vec_perm_1 (enum insn_code icode, rtx target,
5377 rtx v0, rtx v1, rtx sel)
5378{
5379 machine_mode tmode = GET_MODE (target);
5380 machine_mode smode = GET_MODE (sel);
5381 struct expand_operand ops[4];
5382
5383 create_output_operand (&ops[0], target, tmode);
5384 create_input_operand (&ops[3], sel, smode);
5385
5386 /* Make an effort to preserve v0 == v1. The target expander is able to
5387 rely on this to determine if we're permuting a single input operand. */
5388 if (rtx_equal_p (v0, v1))
5389 {
5390 if (!insn_operand_matches (icode, 1, v0))
5391 v0 = force_reg (tmode, v0);
5392 gcc_checking_assert (insn_operand_matches (icode, 1, v0));
5393 gcc_checking_assert (insn_operand_matches (icode, 2, v0));
5394
5395 create_fixed_operand (&ops[1], v0);
5396 create_fixed_operand (&ops[2], v0);
5397 }
5398 else
5399 {
5400 create_input_operand (&ops[1], v0, tmode);
5401 create_input_operand (&ops[2], v1, tmode);
5402 }
5403
5404 if (maybe_expand_insn (icode, 4, ops))
5405 return ops[0].value;
5406 return NULL_RTX;
5407}
5408
5409/* Generate instructions for vec_perm optab given its mode
5410 and three operands. */
5411
5412rtx
5413expand_vec_perm (machine_mode mode, rtx v0, rtx v1, rtx sel, rtx target)
5414{
5415 enum insn_code icode;
5416 machine_mode qimode;
5417 unsigned int i, w, e, u;
5418 rtx tmp, sel_qi = NULL;
5419 rtvec vec;
5420
5421 if (!target || GET_MODE (target) != mode)
5422 target = gen_reg_rtx (mode);
5423
5424 w = GET_MODE_SIZE (mode);
5425 e = GET_MODE_NUNITS (mode);
5426 u = GET_MODE_UNIT_SIZE (mode);
5427
5428 /* Set QIMODE to a different vector mode with byte elements.
5429 If no such mode, or if MODE already has byte elements, use VOIDmode. */
5430 qimode = VOIDmode;
5431 if (GET_MODE_INNER (mode) != QImode)
5432 {
5433 qimode = mode_for_vector (QImode, w);
5434 if (!VECTOR_MODE_P (qimode))
5435 qimode = VOIDmode;
5436 }
5437
5438 /* If the input is a constant, expand it specially. */
5439 gcc_assert (GET_MODE_CLASS (GET_MODE (sel)) == MODE_VECTOR_INT);
5440 if (GET_CODE (sel) == CONST_VECTOR)
5441 {
5442 /* See if this can be handled with a vec_shr. We only do this if the
5443 second vector is all zeroes. */
5444 enum insn_code shift_code = optab_handler (vec_shr_optab, mode);
5445 enum insn_code shift_code_qi = ((qimode != VOIDmode && qimode != mode)
5446 ? optab_handler (vec_shr_optab, qimode)
5447 : CODE_FOR_nothing);
5448 rtx shift_amt = NULL_RTX;
5449 if (v1 == CONST0_RTX (GET_MODE (v1))
5450 && (shift_code != CODE_FOR_nothing
5451 || shift_code_qi != CODE_FOR_nothing))
5452 {
5453 shift_amt = shift_amt_for_vec_perm_mask (sel);
5454 if (shift_amt)
5455 {
5456 struct expand_operand ops[3];
5457 if (shift_code != CODE_FOR_nothing)
5458 {
5459 create_output_operand (&ops[0], target, mode);
5460 create_input_operand (&ops[1], v0, mode);
5461 create_convert_operand_from_type (&ops[2], shift_amt,
5462 sizetype);
5463 if (maybe_expand_insn (shift_code, 3, ops))
5464 return ops[0].value;
5465 }
5466 if (shift_code_qi != CODE_FOR_nothing)
5467 {
5468 tmp = gen_reg_rtx (qimode);
5469 create_output_operand (&ops[0], tmp, qimode);
5470 create_input_operand (&ops[1], gen_lowpart (qimode, v0),
5471 qimode);
5472 create_convert_operand_from_type (&ops[2], shift_amt,
5473 sizetype);
5474 if (maybe_expand_insn (shift_code_qi, 3, ops))
5475 return gen_lowpart (mode, ops[0].value);
5476 }
5477 }
5478 }
5479
5480 icode = direct_optab_handler (vec_perm_const_optab, mode);
5481 if (icode != CODE_FOR_nothing)
5482 {
5483 tmp = expand_vec_perm_1 (icode, target, v0, v1, sel);
5484 if (tmp)
5485 return tmp;
5486 }
5487
5488 /* Fall back to a constant byte-based permutation. */
5489 if (qimode != VOIDmode)
5490 {
5491 vec = rtvec_alloc (w);
5492 for (i = 0; i < e; ++i)
5493 {
5494 unsigned int j, this_e;
5495
5496 this_e = INTVAL (CONST_VECTOR_ELT (sel, i));
5497 this_e &= 2 * e - 1;
5498 this_e *= u;
5499
5500 for (j = 0; j < u; ++j)
5501 RTVEC_ELT (vec, i * u + j) = GEN_INT (this_e + j);
5502 }
5503 sel_qi = gen_rtx_CONST_VECTOR (qimode, vec);
5504
5505 icode = direct_optab_handler (vec_perm_const_optab, qimode);
5506 if (icode != CODE_FOR_nothing)
5507 {
5508 tmp = mode != qimode ? gen_reg_rtx (qimode) : target;
5509 tmp = expand_vec_perm_1 (icode, tmp, gen_lowpart (qimode, v0),
5510 gen_lowpart (qimode, v1), sel_qi);
5511 if (tmp)
5512 return gen_lowpart (mode, tmp);
5513 }
5514 }
5515 }
5516
5517 /* Otherwise expand as a fully variable permuation. */
5518 icode = direct_optab_handler (vec_perm_optab, mode);
5519 if (icode != CODE_FOR_nothing)
5520 {
5521 tmp = expand_vec_perm_1 (icode, target, v0, v1, sel);
5522 if (tmp)
5523 return tmp;
5524 }
5525
5526 /* As a special case to aid several targets, lower the element-based
5527 permutation to a byte-based permutation and try again. */
5528 if (qimode == VOIDmode)
5529 return NULL_RTX;
5530 icode = direct_optab_handler (vec_perm_optab, qimode);
5531 if (icode == CODE_FOR_nothing)
5532 return NULL_RTX;
5533
5534 if (sel_qi == NULL)
5535 {
5536 /* Multiply each element by its byte size. */
5537 machine_mode selmode = GET_MODE (sel);
5538 if (u == 2)
5539 sel = expand_simple_binop (selmode, PLUS, sel, sel,
5540 NULL, 0, OPTAB_DIRECT);
5541 else
5542 sel = expand_simple_binop (selmode, ASHIFT, sel,
5543 GEN_INT (exact_log2 (u)),
5544 NULL, 0, OPTAB_DIRECT);
5545 gcc_assert (sel != NULL);
5546
5547 /* Broadcast the low byte each element into each of its bytes. */
5548 vec = rtvec_alloc (w);
5549 for (i = 0; i < w; ++i)
5550 {
5551 int this_e = i / u * u;
5552 if (BYTES_BIG_ENDIAN)
5553 this_e += u - 1;
5554 RTVEC_ELT (vec, i) = GEN_INT (this_e);
5555 }
5556 tmp = gen_rtx_CONST_VECTOR (qimode, vec);
5557 sel = gen_lowpart (qimode, sel);
5558 sel = expand_vec_perm (qimode, sel, sel, tmp, NULL);
5559 gcc_assert (sel != NULL);
5560
5561 /* Add the byte offset to each byte element. */
5562 /* Note that the definition of the indicies here is memory ordering,
5563 so there should be no difference between big and little endian. */
5564 vec = rtvec_alloc (w);
5565 for (i = 0; i < w; ++i)
5566 RTVEC_ELT (vec, i) = GEN_INT (i % u);
5567 tmp = gen_rtx_CONST_VECTOR (qimode, vec);
5568 sel_qi = expand_simple_binop (qimode, PLUS, sel, tmp,
5569 sel, 0, OPTAB_DIRECT);
5570 gcc_assert (sel_qi != NULL);
5571 }
5572
5573 tmp = mode != qimode ? gen_reg_rtx (qimode) : target;
5574 tmp = expand_vec_perm_1 (icode, tmp, gen_lowpart (qimode, v0),
5575 gen_lowpart (qimode, v1), sel_qi);
5576 if (tmp)
5577 tmp = gen_lowpart (mode, tmp);
5578 return tmp;
5579}
5580
5581/* Generate insns for a VEC_COND_EXPR with mask, given its TYPE and its
5582 three operands. */
5583
5584rtx
5585expand_vec_cond_mask_expr (tree vec_cond_type, tree op0, tree op1, tree op2,
5586 rtx target)
5587{
5588 struct expand_operand ops[4];
5589 machine_mode mode = TYPE_MODE (vec_cond_type);
5590 machine_mode mask_mode = TYPE_MODE (TREE_TYPE (op0));
5591 enum insn_code icode = get_vcond_mask_icode (mode, mask_mode);
5592 rtx mask, rtx_op1, rtx_op2;
5593
5594 if (icode == CODE_FOR_nothing)
5595 return 0;
5596
5597 mask = expand_normal (op0);
5598 rtx_op1 = expand_normal (op1);
5599 rtx_op2 = expand_normal (op2);
5600
5601 mask = force_reg (mask_mode, mask);
5602 rtx_op1 = force_reg (GET_MODE (rtx_op1), rtx_op1);
5603
5604 create_output_operand (&ops[0], target, mode);
5605 create_input_operand (&ops[1], rtx_op1, mode);
5606 create_input_operand (&ops[2], rtx_op2, mode);
5607 create_input_operand (&ops[3], mask, mask_mode);
5608 expand_insn (icode, 4, ops);
5609
5610 return ops[0].value;
5611}
5612
5613/* Generate insns for a VEC_COND_EXPR, given its TYPE and its
5614 three operands. */
5615
5616rtx
5617expand_vec_cond_expr (tree vec_cond_type, tree op0, tree op1, tree op2,
5618 rtx target)
5619{
5620 struct expand_operand ops[6];
5621 enum insn_code icode;
5622 rtx comparison, rtx_op1, rtx_op2;
5623 machine_mode mode = TYPE_MODE (vec_cond_type);
5624 machine_mode cmp_op_mode;
5625 bool unsignedp;
5626 tree op0a, op0b;
5627 enum tree_code tcode;
5628
5629 if (COMPARISON_CLASS_P (op0))
5630 {
5631 op0a = TREE_OPERAND (op0, 0);
5632 op0b = TREE_OPERAND (op0, 1);
5633 tcode = TREE_CODE (op0);
5634 }
5635 else
5636 {
5637 gcc_assert (VECTOR_BOOLEAN_TYPE_P (TREE_TYPE (op0)));
5638 if (get_vcond_mask_icode (mode, TYPE_MODE (TREE_TYPE (op0)))
5639 != CODE_FOR_nothing)
5640 return expand_vec_cond_mask_expr (vec_cond_type, op0, op1,
5641 op2, target);
5642 /* Fake op0 < 0. */
5643 else
5644 {
5645 gcc_assert (GET_MODE_CLASS (TYPE_MODE (TREE_TYPE (op0)))
5646 == MODE_VECTOR_INT);
5647 op0a = op0;
5648 op0b = build_zero_cst (TREE_TYPE (op0));
5649 tcode = LT_EXPR;
5650 }
5651 }
5652 cmp_op_mode = TYPE_MODE (TREE_TYPE (op0a));
5653 unsignedp = TYPE_UNSIGNED (TREE_TYPE (op0a));
5654
5655
5656 gcc_assert (GET_MODE_SIZE (mode) == GET_MODE_SIZE (cmp_op_mode)
5657 && GET_MODE_NUNITS (mode) == GET_MODE_NUNITS (cmp_op_mode));
5658
5659 icode = get_vcond_icode (mode, cmp_op_mode, unsignedp);
5660 if (icode == CODE_FOR_nothing)
5661 {
5662 if (tcode == EQ_EXPR || tcode == NE_EXPR)
5663 icode = get_vcond_eq_icode (mode, cmp_op_mode);
5664 if (icode == CODE_FOR_nothing)
5665 return 0;
5666 }
5667
5668 comparison = vector_compare_rtx (VOIDmode, tcode, op0a, op0b, unsignedp,
5669 icode, 4);
5670 rtx_op1 = expand_normal (op1);
5671 rtx_op2 = expand_normal (op2);
5672
5673 create_output_operand (&ops[0], target, mode);
5674 create_input_operand (&ops[1], rtx_op1, mode);
5675 create_input_operand (&ops[2], rtx_op2, mode);
5676 create_fixed_operand (&ops[3], comparison);
5677 create_fixed_operand (&ops[4], XEXP (comparison, 0));
5678 create_fixed_operand (&ops[5], XEXP (comparison, 1));
5679 expand_insn (icode, 6, ops);
5680 return ops[0].value;
5681}
5682
5683/* Generate insns for a vector comparison into a mask. */
5684
5685rtx
5686expand_vec_cmp_expr (tree type, tree exp, rtx target)
5687{
5688 struct expand_operand ops[4];
5689 enum insn_code icode;
5690 rtx comparison;
5691 machine_mode mask_mode = TYPE_MODE (type);
5692 machine_mode vmode;
5693 bool unsignedp;
5694 tree op0a, op0b;
5695 enum tree_code tcode;
5696
5697 op0a = TREE_OPERAND (exp, 0);
5698 op0b = TREE_OPERAND (exp, 1);
5699 tcode = TREE_CODE (exp);
5700
5701 unsignedp = TYPE_UNSIGNED (TREE_TYPE (op0a));
5702 vmode = TYPE_MODE (TREE_TYPE (op0a));
5703
5704 icode = get_vec_cmp_icode (vmode, mask_mode, unsignedp);
5705 if (icode == CODE_FOR_nothing)
5706 {
5707 if (tcode == EQ_EXPR || tcode == NE_EXPR)
5708 icode = get_vec_cmp_eq_icode (vmode, mask_mode);
5709 if (icode == CODE_FOR_nothing)
5710 return 0;
5711 }
5712
5713 comparison = vector_compare_rtx (mask_mode, tcode, op0a, op0b,
5714 unsignedp, icode, 2);
5715 create_output_operand (&ops[0], target, mask_mode);
5716 create_fixed_operand (&ops[1], comparison);
5717 create_fixed_operand (&ops[2], XEXP (comparison, 0));
5718 create_fixed_operand (&ops[3], XEXP (comparison, 1));
5719 expand_insn (icode, 4, ops);
5720 return ops[0].value;
5721}
5722
5723/* Expand a highpart multiply. */
5724
5725rtx
5726expand_mult_highpart (machine_mode mode, rtx op0, rtx op1,
5727 rtx target, bool uns_p)
5728{
5729 struct expand_operand eops[3];
5730 enum insn_code icode;
5731 int method, i, nunits;
5732 machine_mode wmode;
5733 rtx m1, m2, perm;
5734 optab tab1, tab2;
5735 rtvec v;
5736
5737 method = can_mult_highpart_p (mode, uns_p);
5738 switch (method)
5739 {
5740 case 0:
5741 return NULL_RTX;
5742 case 1:
5743 tab1 = uns_p ? umul_highpart_optab : smul_highpart_optab;
5744 return expand_binop (mode, tab1, op0, op1, target, uns_p,
5745 OPTAB_LIB_WIDEN);
5746 case 2:
5747 tab1 = uns_p ? vec_widen_umult_even_optab : vec_widen_smult_even_optab;
5748 tab2 = uns_p ? vec_widen_umult_odd_optab : vec_widen_smult_odd_optab;
5749 break;
5750 case 3:
5751 tab1 = uns_p ? vec_widen_umult_lo_optab : vec_widen_smult_lo_optab;
5752 tab2 = uns_p ? vec_widen_umult_hi_optab : vec_widen_smult_hi_optab;
5753 if (BYTES_BIG_ENDIAN)
5754 std::swap (tab1, tab2);
5755 break;
5756 default:
5757 gcc_unreachable ();
5758 }
5759
5760 icode = optab_handler (tab1, mode);
5761 nunits = GET_MODE_NUNITS (mode);
5762 wmode = insn_data[icode].operand[0].mode;
5763 gcc_checking_assert (2 * GET_MODE_NUNITS (wmode) == nunits);
5764 gcc_checking_assert (GET_MODE_SIZE (wmode) == GET_MODE_SIZE (mode));
5765
5766 create_output_operand (&eops[0], gen_reg_rtx (wmode), wmode);
5767 create_input_operand (&eops[1], op0, mode);
5768 create_input_operand (&eops[2], op1, mode);
5769 expand_insn (icode, 3, eops);
5770 m1 = gen_lowpart (mode, eops[0].value);
5771
5772 create_output_operand (&eops[0], gen_reg_rtx (wmode), wmode);
5773 create_input_operand (&eops[1], op0, mode);
5774 create_input_operand (&eops[2], op1, mode);
5775 expand_insn (optab_handler (tab2, mode), 3, eops);
5776 m2 = gen_lowpart (mode, eops[0].value);
5777
5778 v = rtvec_alloc (nunits);
5779 if (method == 2)
5780 {
5781 for (i = 0; i < nunits; ++i)
5782 RTVEC_ELT (v, i) = GEN_INT (!BYTES_BIG_ENDIAN + (i & ~1)
5783 + ((i & 1) ? nunits : 0));
5784 }
5785 else
5786 {
5787 for (i = 0; i < nunits; ++i)
5788 RTVEC_ELT (v, i) = GEN_INT (2 * i + (BYTES_BIG_ENDIAN ? 0 : 1));
5789 }
5790 perm = gen_rtx_CONST_VECTOR (mode, v);
5791
5792 return expand_vec_perm (mode, m1, m2, perm, target);
5793}

5795/* Helper function to find the MODE_CC set in a sync_compare_and_swap
5796 pattern. */
5797
5798static void
5799find_cc_set (rtx x, const_rtx pat, void *data)
5800{
5801 if (REG_P (x) && GET_MODE_CLASS (GET_MODE (x)) == MODE_CC
5802 && GET_CODE (pat) == SET)
5803 {
5804 rtx *p_cc_reg = (rtx *) data;
5805 gcc_assert (!*p_cc_reg);
5806 *p_cc_reg = x;
5807 }
5808}
5809
5810/* This is a helper function for the other atomic operations. This function
5811 emits a loop that contains SEQ that iterates until a compare-and-swap
5812 operation at the end succeeds. MEM is the memory to be modified. SEQ is
5813 a set of instructions that takes a value from OLD_REG as an input and
5814 produces a value in NEW_REG as an output. Before SEQ, OLD_REG will be
5815 set to the current contents of MEM. After SEQ, a compare-and-swap will
5816 attempt to update MEM with NEW_REG. The function returns true when the
5817 loop was generated successfully. */
5818
5819static bool
5820expand_compare_and_swap_loop (rtx mem, rtx old_reg, rtx new_reg, rtx seq)
5821{
5822 machine_mode mode = GET_MODE (mem);
5823 rtx_code_label *label;
5824 rtx cmp_reg, success, oldval;
5825
5826 /* The loop we want to generate looks like
5827
5828 cmp_reg = mem;
5829 label:
5830 old_reg = cmp_reg;
5831 seq;
5832 (success, cmp_reg) = compare-and-swap(mem, old_reg, new_reg)
5833 if (success)
5834 goto label;
5835
5836 Note that we only do the plain load from memory once. Subsequent
5837 iterations use the value loaded by the compare-and-swap pattern. */
5838
5839 label = gen_label_rtx ();
5840 cmp_reg = gen_reg_rtx (mode);
5841
5842 emit_move_insn (cmp_reg, mem);
5843 emit_label (label);
5844 emit_move_insn (old_reg, cmp_reg);
5845 if (seq)
5846 emit_insn (seq);
5847
5848 success = NULL_RTX;
5849 oldval = cmp_reg;
5850 if (!expand_atomic_compare_and_swap (&success, &oldval, mem, old_reg,
5851 new_reg, false, MEMMODEL_SYNC_SEQ_CST,
5852 MEMMODEL_RELAXED))
5853 return false;
5854
5855 if (oldval != cmp_reg)
5856 emit_move_insn (cmp_reg, oldval);
5857
5858 /* Mark this jump predicted not taken. */
5859 emit_cmp_and_jump_insns (success, const0_rtx, EQ, const0_rtx,
5860 GET_MODE (success), 1, label, 0);
5861 return true;
5862}

5865/* This function tries to emit an atomic_exchange intruction. VAL is written
5866 to *MEM using memory model MODEL. The previous contents of *MEM are returned,
5867 using TARGET if possible. */
5868
5869static rtx
5870maybe_emit_atomic_exchange (rtx target, rtx mem, rtx val, enum memmodel model)
5871{
5872 machine_mode mode = GET_MODE (mem);
5873 enum insn_code icode;
5874
5875 /* If the target supports the exchange directly, great. */
5876 icode = direct_optab_handler (atomic_exchange_optab, mode);
5877 if (icode != CODE_FOR_nothing)
5878 {
5879 struct expand_operand ops[4];
5880
5881 create_output_operand (&ops[0], target, mode);
5882 create_fixed_operand (&ops[1], mem);
5883 create_input_operand (&ops[2], val, mode);
5884 create_integer_operand (&ops[3], model);
5885 if (maybe_expand_insn (icode, 4, ops))
5886 return ops[0].value;
5887 }
5888
5889 return NULL_RTX;
5890}
5891
5892/* This function tries to implement an atomic exchange operation using
5893 __sync_lock_test_and_set. VAL is written to *MEM using memory model MODEL.
5894 The previous contents of *MEM are returned, using TARGET if possible.
5895 Since this instructionn is an acquire barrier only, stronger memory
5896 models may require additional barriers to be emitted. */
5897
5898static rtx
5899maybe_emit_sync_lock_test_and_set (rtx target, rtx mem, rtx val,
5900 enum memmodel model)
5901{
5902 machine_mode mode = GET_MODE (mem);
5903 enum insn_code icode;
5904 rtx_insn *last_insn = get_last_insn ();
5905
5906 icode = optab_handler (sync_lock_test_and_set_optab, mode);
5907
5908 /* Legacy sync_lock_test_and_set is an acquire barrier. If the pattern
5909 exists, and the memory model is stronger than acquire, add a release
5910 barrier before the instruction. */
5911
5912 if (is_mm_seq_cst (model) || is_mm_release (model) || is_mm_acq_rel (model))
5913 expand_mem_thread_fence (model);
5914
5915 if (icode != CODE_FOR_nothing)
5916 {
5917 struct expand_operand ops[3];
5918 create_output_operand (&ops[0], target, mode);
5919 create_fixed_operand (&ops[1], mem);
5920 create_input_operand (&ops[2], val, mode);
5921 if (maybe_expand_insn (icode, 3, ops))
5922 return ops[0].value;
5923 }
5924
5925 /* If an external test-and-set libcall is provided, use that instead of
5926 any external compare-and-swap that we might get from the compare-and-
5927 swap-loop expansion later. */
5928 if (!can_compare_and_swap_p (mode, false))
5929 {
5930 rtx libfunc = optab_libfunc (sync_lock_test_and_set_optab, mode);
5931 if (libfunc != NULL)
5932 {
5933 rtx addr;
5934
5935 addr = convert_memory_address (ptr_mode, XEXP (mem, 0));
5936 return emit_library_call_value (libfunc, NULL_RTX, LCT_NORMAL,
5937 mode, 2, addr, ptr_mode,
5938 val, mode);
5939 }
5940 }
5941
5942 /* If the test_and_set can't be emitted, eliminate any barrier that might
5943 have been emitted. */
5944 delete_insns_since (last_insn);
5945 return NULL_RTX;
5946}
5947
5948/* This function tries to implement an atomic exchange operation using a
5949 compare_and_swap loop. VAL is written to *MEM. The previous contents of
5950 *MEM are returned, using TARGET if possible. No memory model is required
5951 since a compare_and_swap loop is seq-cst. */
5952
5953static rtx
5954maybe_emit_compare_and_swap_exchange_loop (rtx target, rtx mem, rtx val)
5955{
5956 machine_mode mode = GET_MODE (mem);
5957
5958 if (can_compare_and_swap_p (mode, true))
5959 {
5960 if (!target || !register_operand (target, mode))
5961 target = gen_reg_rtx (mode);
5962 if (expand_compare_and_swap_loop (mem, target, val, NULL_RTX))
5963 return target;
5964 }
5965
5966 return NULL_RTX;
5967}
5968
5969/* This function tries to implement an atomic test-and-set operation
5970 using the atomic_test_and_set instruction pattern. A boolean value
5971 is returned from the operation, using TARGET if possible. */
5972
5973static rtx
5974maybe_emit_atomic_test_and_set (rtx target, rtx mem, enum memmodel model)
5975{
5976 machine_mode pat_bool_mode;
5977 struct expand_operand ops[3];
5978
5979 if (!targetm.have_atomic_test_and_set ())
5980 return NULL_RTX;
5981
5982 /* While we always get QImode from __atomic_test_and_set, we get
5983 other memory modes from __sync_lock_test_and_set. Note that we
5984 use no endian adjustment here. This matches the 4.6 behavior
5985 in the Sparc backend. */
5986 enum insn_code icode = targetm.code_for_atomic_test_and_set;
5987 gcc_checking_assert (insn_data[icode].operand[1].mode == QImode);
5988 if (GET_MODE (mem) != QImode)
5989 mem = adjust_address_nv (mem, QImode, 0);
5990
5991 pat_bool_mode = insn_data[icode].operand[0].mode;
5992 create_output_operand (&ops[0], target, pat_bool_mode);
5993 create_fixed_operand (&ops[1], mem);
5994 create_integer_operand (&ops[2], model);
5995
5996 if (maybe_expand_insn (icode, 3, ops))
5997 return ops[0].value;
5998 return NULL_RTX;
5999}
6000
6001/* This function expands the legacy _sync_lock test_and_set operation which is
6002 generally an atomic exchange. Some limited targets only allow the
6003 constant 1 to be stored. This is an ACQUIRE operation.
6004
6005 TARGET is an optional place to stick the return value.
6006 MEM is where VAL is stored. */
6007
6008rtx
6009expand_sync_lock_test_and_set (rtx target, rtx mem, rtx val)
6010{
6011 rtx ret;
6012
6013 /* Try an atomic_exchange first. */
6014 ret = maybe_emit_atomic_exchange (target, mem, val, MEMMODEL_SYNC_ACQUIRE);
6015 if (ret)
6016 return ret;
6017
6018 ret = maybe_emit_sync_lock_test_and_set (target, mem, val,
6019 MEMMODEL_SYNC_ACQUIRE);
6020 if (ret)
6021 return ret;
6022
6023 ret = maybe_emit_compare_and_swap_exchange_loop (target, mem, val);
6024 if (ret)
6025 return ret;
6026
6027 /* If there are no other options, try atomic_test_and_set if the value
6028 being stored is 1. */
6029 if (val == const1_rtx)
6030 ret = maybe_emit_atomic_test_and_set (target, mem, MEMMODEL_SYNC_ACQUIRE);
6031
6032 return ret;
6033}
6034
6035/* This function expands the atomic test_and_set operation:
6036 atomically store a boolean TRUE into MEM and return the previous value.
6037
6038 MEMMODEL is the memory model variant to use.
6039 TARGET is an optional place to stick the return value. */
6040
6041rtx
6042expand_atomic_test_and_set (rtx target, rtx mem, enum memmodel model)
6043{
6044 machine_mode mode = GET_MODE (mem);
6045 rtx ret, trueval, subtarget;
6046
6047 ret = maybe_emit_atomic_test_and_set (target, mem, model);
6048 if (ret)
6049 return ret;
6050
6051 /* Be binary compatible with non-default settings of trueval, and different
6052 cpu revisions. E.g. one revision may have atomic-test-and-set, but
6053 another only has atomic-exchange. */
6054 if (targetm.atomic_test_and_set_trueval == 1)
6055 {
6056 trueval = const1_rtx;
6057 subtarget = target ? target : gen_reg_rtx (mode);
6058 }
6059 else
6060 {
6061 trueval = gen_int_mode (targetm.atomic_test_and_set_trueval, mode);
6062 subtarget = gen_reg_rtx (mode);
6063 }
6064
6065 /* Try the atomic-exchange optab... */
6066 ret = maybe_emit_atomic_exchange (subtarget, mem, trueval, model);
6067
6068 /* ... then an atomic-compare-and-swap loop ... */
6069 if (!ret)
6070 ret = maybe_emit_compare_and_swap_exchange_loop (subtarget, mem, trueval);
6071
6072 /* ... before trying the vaguely defined legacy lock_test_and_set. */
6073 if (!ret)
6074 ret = maybe_emit_sync_lock_test_and_set (subtarget, mem, trueval, model);
6075
6076 /* Recall that the legacy lock_test_and_set optab was allowed to do magic
6077 things with the value 1. Thus we try again without trueval. */
6078 if (!ret && targetm.atomic_test_and_set_trueval != 1)
6079 ret = maybe_emit_sync_lock_test_and_set (subtarget, mem, const1_rtx, model);
6080
6081 /* Failing all else, assume a single threaded environment and simply
6082 perform the operation. */
6083 if (!ret)
6084 {
6085 /* If the result is ignored skip the move to target. */
6086 if (subtarget != const0_rtx)
6087 emit_move_insn (subtarget, mem);
6088
6089 emit_move_insn (mem, trueval);
6090 ret = subtarget;
6091 }
6092
6093 /* Recall that have to return a boolean value; rectify if trueval
6094 is not exactly one. */
6095 if (targetm.atomic_test_and_set_trueval != 1)
6096 ret = emit_store_flag_force (target, NE, ret, const0_rtx, mode, 0, 1);
6097
6098 return ret;
6099}
6100
6101/* This function expands the atomic exchange operation:
6102 atomically store VAL in MEM and return the previous value in MEM.
6103
6104 MEMMODEL is the memory model variant to use.
6105 TARGET is an optional place to stick the return value. */
6106
6107rtx
6108expand_atomic_exchange (rtx target, rtx mem, rtx val, enum memmodel model)
6109{
6110 machine_mode mode = GET_MODE (mem);
6111 rtx ret;
6112
6113 /* If loads are not atomic for the required size and we are not called to
6114 provide a __sync builtin, do not do anything so that we stay consistent
6115 with atomic loads of the same size. */
6116 if (!can_atomic_load_p (mode) && !is_mm_sync (model))
6117 return NULL_RTX;
6118
6119 ret = maybe_emit_atomic_exchange (target, mem, val, model);
6120
6121 /* Next try a compare-and-swap loop for the exchange. */
6122 if (!ret)
6123 ret = maybe_emit_compare_and_swap_exchange_loop (target, mem, val);
6124
6125 return ret;
6126}
6127
6128/* This function expands the atomic compare exchange operation:
6129
6130 *PTARGET_BOOL is an optional place to store the boolean success/failure.
6131 *PTARGET_OVAL is an optional place to store the old value from memory.
6132 Both target parameters may be NULL or const0_rtx to indicate that we do
6133 not care about that return value. Both target parameters are updated on
6134 success to the actual location of the corresponding result.
6135
6136 MEMMODEL is the memory model variant to use.
6137
6138 The return value of the function is true for success. */
6139
6140bool
6141expand_atomic_compare_and_swap (rtx *ptarget_bool, rtx *ptarget_oval,
6142 rtx mem, rtx expected, rtx desired,
6143 bool is_weak, enum memmodel succ_model,
6144 enum memmodel fail_model)
6145{
6146 machine_mode mode = GET_MODE (mem);
6147 struct expand_operand ops[8];
6148 enum insn_code icode;
6149 rtx target_oval, target_bool = NULL_RTX;
6150 rtx libfunc;
6151
6152 /* If loads are not atomic for the required size and we are not called to
6153 provide a __sync builtin, do not do anything so that we stay consistent
6154 with atomic loads of the same size. */
6155 if (!can_atomic_load_p (mode) && !is_mm_sync (succ_model))
6156 return false;
6157
6158 /* Load expected into a register for the compare and swap. */
6159 if (MEM_P (expected))
6160 expected = copy_to_reg (expected);
6161
6162 /* Make sure we always have some place to put the return oldval.
6163 Further, make sure that place is distinct from the input expected,
6164 just in case we need that path down below. */
6165 if (ptarget_oval && *ptarget_oval == const0_rtx)
6166 ptarget_oval = NULL;
6167
6168 if (ptarget_oval == NULL
6169 || (target_oval = *ptarget_oval) == NULL
6170 || reg_overlap_mentioned_p (expected, target_oval))
6171 target_oval = gen_reg_rtx (mode);
6172
6173 icode = direct_optab_handler (atomic_compare_and_swap_optab, mode);
6174 if (icode != CODE_FOR_nothing)
6175 {
6176 machine_mode bool_mode = insn_data[icode].operand[0].mode;
6177
6178 if (ptarget_bool && *ptarget_bool == const0_rtx)
6179 ptarget_bool = NULL;
6180
6181 /* Make sure we always have a place for the bool operand. */
6182 if (ptarget_bool == NULL
6183 || (target_bool = *ptarget_bool) == NULL
6184 || GET_MODE (target_bool) != bool_mode)
6185 target_bool = gen_reg_rtx (bool_mode);
6186
6187 /* Emit the compare_and_swap. */
6188 create_output_operand (&ops[0], target_bool, bool_mode);
6189 create_output_operand (&ops[1], target_oval, mode);
6190 create_fixed_operand (&ops[2], mem);
6191 create_input_operand (&ops[3], expected, mode);
6192 create_input_operand (&ops[4], desired, mode);
6193 create_integer_operand (&ops[5], is_weak);
6194 create_integer_operand (&ops[6], succ_model);
6195 create_integer_operand (&ops[7], fail_model);
6196 if (maybe_expand_insn (icode, 8, ops))
6197 {
6198 /* Return success/failure. */
6199 target_bool = ops[0].value;
6200 target_oval = ops[1].value;
6201 goto success;
6202 }
6203 }
6204
6205 /* Otherwise fall back to the original __sync_val_compare_and_swap
6206 which is always seq-cst. */
6207 icode = optab_handler (sync_compare_and_swap_optab, mode);
6208 if (icode != CODE_FOR_nothing)
6209 {
6210 rtx cc_reg;
6211
6212 create_output_operand (&ops[0], target_oval, mode);
6213 create_fixed_operand (&ops[1], mem);
6214 create_input_operand (&ops[2], expected, mode);
6215 create_input_operand (&ops[3], desired, mode);
6216 if (!maybe_expand_insn (icode, 4, ops))
6217 return false;
6218
6219 target_oval = ops[0].value;
6220
6221 /* If the caller isn't interested in the boolean return value,
6222 skip the computation of it. */
6223 if (ptarget_bool == NULL)
6224 goto success;
6225
6226 /* Otherwise, work out if the compare-and-swap succeeded. */
6227 cc_reg = NULL_RTX;
6228 if (have_insn_for (COMPARE, CCmode))
6229 note_stores (PATTERN (get_last_insn ()), find_cc_set, &cc_reg);
6230 if (cc_reg)
6231 {
6232 target_bool = emit_store_flag_force (target_bool, EQ, cc_reg,
6233 const0_rtx, VOIDmode, 0, 1);
6234 goto success;
6235 }
6236 goto success_bool_from_val;
6237 }
6238
6239 /* Also check for library support for __sync_val_compare_and_swap. */
6240 libfunc = optab_libfunc (sync_compare_and_swap_optab, mode);
6241 if (libfunc != NULL)
6242 {
6243 rtx addr = convert_memory_address (ptr_mode, XEXP (mem, 0));
6244 rtx target = emit_library_call_value (libfunc, NULL_RTX, LCT_NORMAL,
6245 mode, 3, addr, ptr_mode,
6246 expected, mode, desired, mode);
6247 emit_move_insn (target_oval, target);
6248
6249 /* Compute the boolean return value only if requested. */
6250 if (ptarget_bool)
6251 goto success_bool_from_val;
6252 else
6253 goto success;
6254 }
6255
6256 /* Failure. */
6257 return false;
6258
6259 success_bool_from_val:
6260 target_bool = emit_store_flag_force (target_bool, EQ, target_oval,
6261 expected, VOIDmode, 1, 1);
6262 success:
6263 /* Make sure that the oval output winds up where the caller asked. */
6264 if (ptarget_oval)
6265 *ptarget_oval = target_oval;
6266 if (ptarget_bool)
6267 *ptarget_bool = target_bool;
6268 return true;
6269}

6271/* Generate asm volatile("" : : : "memory") as the memory barrier. */
6272
6273static void
6274expand_asm_memory_barrier (void)
6275{
6276 rtx asm_op, clob;
6277
6278 asm_op = gen_rtx_ASM_OPERANDS (VOIDmode, empty_string, empty_string, 0,
6279 rtvec_alloc (0), rtvec_alloc (0),
6280 rtvec_alloc (0), UNKNOWN_LOCATION);
6281 MEM_VOLATILE_P (asm_op) = 1;
6282
6283 clob = gen_rtx_SCRATCH (VOIDmode);
6284 clob = gen_rtx_MEM (BLKmode, clob);
6285 clob = gen_rtx_CLOBBER (VOIDmode, clob);
6286
6287 emit_insn (gen_rtx_PARALLEL (VOIDmode, gen_rtvec (2, asm_op, clob)));
6288}
6289
6290/* This routine will either emit the mem_thread_fence pattern or issue a
6291 sync_synchronize to generate a fence for memory model MEMMODEL. */
6292
6293void
6294expand_mem_thread_fence (enum memmodel model)
6295{
6296 if (targetm.have_mem_thread_fence ())
6297 emit_insn (targetm.gen_mem_thread_fence (GEN_INT (model)));
6298 else if (!is_mm_relaxed (model))
6299 {
6300 if (targetm.have_memory_barrier ())
6301 emit_insn (targetm.gen_memory_barrier ());
6302 else if (synchronize_libfunc != NULL_RTX)
6303 emit_library_call (synchronize_libfunc, LCT_NORMAL, VOIDmode, 0);
6304 else
6305 expand_asm_memory_barrier ();
6306 }
6307}
6308
6309/* This routine will either emit the mem_signal_fence pattern or issue a
6310 sync_synchronize to generate a fence for memory model MEMMODEL. */
6311
6312void
6313expand_mem_signal_fence (enum memmodel model)
6314{
6315 if (targetm.have_mem_signal_fence ())
6316 emit_insn (targetm.gen_mem_signal_fence (GEN_INT (model)));
6317 else if (!is_mm_relaxed (model))
6318 {
6319 /* By default targets are coherent between a thread and the signal
6320 handler running on the same thread. Thus this really becomes a
6321 compiler barrier, in that stores must not be sunk past
6322 (or raised above) a given point. */
6323 expand_asm_memory_barrier ();
6324 }
6325}
6326
6327/* This function expands the atomic load operation:
6328 return the atomically loaded value in MEM.
6329
6330 MEMMODEL is the memory model variant to use.
6331 TARGET is an option place to stick the return value. */
6332
6333rtx
6334expand_atomic_load (rtx target, rtx mem, enum memmodel model)
6335{
6336 machine_mode mode = GET_MODE (mem);
6337 enum insn_code icode;
6338
6339 /* If the target supports the load directly, great. */
6340 icode = direct_optab_handler (atomic_load_optab, mode);
6341 if (icode != CODE_FOR_nothing)
6342 {
6343 struct expand_operand ops[3];
6344
6345 create_output_operand (&ops[0], target, mode);
6346 create_fixed_operand (&ops[1], mem);
6347 create_integer_operand (&ops[2], model);
6348 if (maybe_expand_insn (icode, 3, ops))
6349 return ops[0].value;
6350 }
6351
6352 /* If the size of the object is greater than word size on this target,
6353 then we assume that a load will not be atomic. We could try to
6354 emulate a load with a compare-and-swap operation, but the store that
6355 doing this could result in would be incorrect if this is a volatile
6356 atomic load or targetting read-only-mapped memory. */
6357 if (GET_MODE_PRECISION (mode) > BITS_PER_WORD)
6358 /* If there is no atomic load, leave the library call. */
6359 return NULL_RTX;
6360
6361 /* Otherwise assume loads are atomic, and emit the proper barriers. */
6362 if (!target || target == const0_rtx)
6363 target = gen_reg_rtx (mode);
6364
6365 /* For SEQ_CST, emit a barrier before the load. */
6366 if (is_mm_seq_cst (model))
6367 expand_mem_thread_fence (model);
6368
6369 emit_move_insn (target, mem);
6370
6371 /* Emit the appropriate barrier after the load. */
6372 expand_mem_thread_fence (model);
6373
6374 return target;
6375}
6376
6377/* This function expands the atomic store operation:
6378 Atomically store VAL in MEM.
6379 MEMMODEL is the memory model variant to use.
6380 USE_RELEASE is true if __sync_lock_release can be used as a fall back.
6381 function returns const0_rtx if a pattern was emitted. */
6382
6383rtx
6384expand_atomic_store (rtx mem, rtx val, enum memmodel model, bool use_release)
6385{
6386 machine_mode mode = GET_MODE (mem);
6387 enum insn_code icode;
6388 struct expand_operand ops[3];
6389
6390 /* If the target supports the store directly, great. */
6391 icode = direct_optab_handler (atomic_store_optab, mode);
6392 if (icode != CODE_FOR_nothing)
6393 {
6394 create_fixed_operand (&ops[0], mem);
6395 create_input_operand (&ops[1], val, mode);
6396 create_integer_operand (&ops[2], model);
6397 if (maybe_expand_insn (icode, 3, ops))
6398 return const0_rtx;
6399 }
6400
6401 /* If using __sync_lock_release is a viable alternative, try it.
6402 Note that this will not be set to true if we are expanding a generic
6403 __atomic_store_n. */
6404 if (use_release)
6405 {
6406 icode = direct_optab_handler (sync_lock_release_optab, mode);
6407 if (icode != CODE_FOR_nothing)
6408 {
6409 create_fixed_operand (&ops[0], mem);
6410 create_input_operand (&ops[1], const0_rtx, mode);
6411 if (maybe_expand_insn (icode, 2, ops))
6412 {
6413 /* lock_release is only a release barrier. */
6414 if (is_mm_seq_cst (model))
6415 expand_mem_thread_fence (model);
6416 return const0_rtx;
6417 }
6418 }
6419 }
6420
6421 /* If the size of the object is greater than word size on this target,
6422 a default store will not be atomic. */
6423 if (GET_MODE_PRECISION (mode) > BITS_PER_WORD)
6424 {
6425 /* If loads are atomic or we are called to provide a __sync builtin,
6426 we can try a atomic_exchange and throw away the result. Otherwise,
6427 don't do anything so that we do not create an inconsistency between
6428 loads and stores. */
6429 if (can_atomic_load_p (mode) || is_mm_sync (model))
6430 {
6431 rtx target = maybe_emit_atomic_exchange (NULL_RTX, mem, val, model);
6432 if (!target)
6433 target = maybe_emit_compare_and_swap_exchange_loop (NULL_RTX, mem,
6434 val);
6435 if (target)
6436 return const0_rtx;
6437 }
6438 return NULL_RTX;
6439 }
6440
6441 /* Otherwise assume stores are atomic, and emit the proper barriers. */
6442 expand_mem_thread_fence (model);
6443
6444 emit_move_insn (mem, val);
6445
6446 /* For SEQ_CST, also emit a barrier after the store. */
6447 if (is_mm_seq_cst (model))
6448 expand_mem_thread_fence (model);
6449
6450 return const0_rtx;
6451}
6452
6453
6454/* Structure containing the pointers and values required to process the
6455 various forms of the atomic_fetch_op and atomic_op_fetch builtins. */
6456
6457struct atomic_op_functions
6458{
6459 direct_optab mem_fetch_before;
6460 direct_optab mem_fetch_after;
6461 direct_optab mem_no_result;
6462 optab fetch_before;
6463 optab fetch_after;
6464 direct_optab no_result;
6465 enum rtx_code reverse_code;
6466};
6467
6468
6469/* Fill in structure pointed to by OP with the various optab entries for an
6470 operation of type CODE. */
6471
6472static void
6473get_atomic_op_for_code (struct atomic_op_functions *op, enum rtx_code code)
6474{
6475 gcc_assert (op!= NULL);
6476
6477 /* If SWITCHABLE_TARGET is defined, then subtargets can be switched
6478 in the source code during compilation, and the optab entries are not
6479 computable until runtime. Fill in the values at runtime. */
6480 switch (code)
6481 {
6482 case PLUS:
6483 op->mem_fetch_before = atomic_fetch_add_optab;
6484 op->mem_fetch_after = atomic_add_fetch_optab;
6485 op->mem_no_result = atomic_add_optab;
6486 op->fetch_before = sync_old_add_optab;
6487 op->fetch_after = sync_new_add_optab;
6488 op->no_result = sync_add_optab;
6489 op->reverse_code = MINUS;
6490 break;
6491 case MINUS:
6492 op->mem_fetch_before = atomic_fetch_sub_optab;
6493 op->mem_fetch_after = atomic_sub_fetch_optab;
6494 op->mem_no_result = atomic_sub_optab;
6495 op->fetch_before = sync_old_sub_optab;
6496 op->fetch_after = sync_new_sub_optab;
6497 op->no_result = sync_sub_optab;
6498 op->reverse_code = PLUS;
6499 break;
6500 case XOR:
6501 op->mem_fetch_before = atomic_fetch_xor_optab;
6502 op->mem_fetch_after = atomic_xor_fetch_optab;
6503 op->mem_no_result = atomic_xor_optab;
6504 op->fetch_before = sync_old_xor_optab;
6505 op->fetch_after = sync_new_xor_optab;
6506 op->no_result = sync_xor_optab;
6507 op->reverse_code = XOR;
6508 break;
6509 case AND:
6510 op->mem_fetch_before = atomic_fetch_and_optab;
6511 op->mem_fetch_after = atomic_and_fetch_optab;
6512 op->mem_no_result = atomic_and_optab;
6513 op->fetch_before = sync_old_and_optab;
6514 op->fetch_after = sync_new_and_optab;
6515 op->no_result = sync_and_optab;
6516 op->reverse_code = UNKNOWN;
6517 break;
6518 case IOR:
6519 op->mem_fetch_before = atomic_fetch_or_optab;
6520 op->mem_fetch_after = atomic_or_fetch_optab;
6521 op->mem_no_result = atomic_or_optab;
6522 op->fetch_before = sync_old_ior_optab;
6523 op->fetch_after = sync_new_ior_optab;
6524 op->no_result = sync_ior_optab;
6525 op->reverse_code = UNKNOWN;
6526 break;
6527 case NOT:
6528 op->mem_fetch_before = atomic_fetch_nand_optab;
6529 op->mem_fetch_after = atomic_nand_fetch_optab;
6530 op->mem_no_result = atomic_nand_optab;
6531 op->fetch_before = sync_old_nand_optab;
6532 op->fetch_after = sync_new_nand_optab;
6533 op->no_result = sync_nand_optab;
6534 op->reverse_code = UNKNOWN;
6535 break;
6536 default:
6537 gcc_unreachable ();
6538 }
6539}
6540
6541/* See if there is a more optimal way to implement the operation "*MEM CODE VAL"
6542 using memory order MODEL. If AFTER is true the operation needs to return
6543 the value of *MEM after the operation, otherwise the previous value.
6544 TARGET is an optional place to place the result. The result is unused if
6545 it is const0_rtx.
6546 Return the result if there is a better sequence, otherwise NULL_RTX. */
6547
6548static rtx
6549maybe_optimize_fetch_op (rtx target, rtx mem, rtx val, enum rtx_code code,
6550 enum memmodel model, bool after)
6551{
6552 /* If the value is prefetched, or not used, it may be possible to replace
6553 the sequence with a native exchange operation. */
6554 if (!after || target == const0_rtx)
6555 {
6556 /* fetch_and (&x, 0, m) can be replaced with exchange (&x, 0, m). */
6557 if (code == AND && val == const0_rtx)
6558 {
6559 if (target == const0_rtx)
6560 target = gen_reg_rtx (GET_MODE (mem));
6561 return maybe_emit_atomic_exchange (target, mem, val, model);
6562 }
6563
6564 /* fetch_or (&x, -1, m) can be replaced with exchange (&x, -1, m). */
6565 if (code == IOR && val == constm1_rtx)
6566 {
6567 if (target == const0_rtx)
6568 target = gen_reg_rtx (GET_MODE (mem));
6569 return maybe_emit_atomic_exchange (target, mem, val, model);
6570 }
6571 }
6572
6573 return NULL_RTX;
6574}
6575
6576/* Try to emit an instruction for a specific operation varaition.
6577 OPTAB contains the OP functions.
6578 TARGET is an optional place to return the result. const0_rtx means unused.
6579 MEM is the memory location to operate on.
6580 VAL is the value to use in the operation.
6581 USE_MEMMODEL is TRUE if the variation with a memory model should be tried.
6582 MODEL is the memory model, if used.
6583 AFTER is true if the returned result is the value after the operation. */
6584
6585static rtx
6586maybe_emit_op (const struct atomic_op_functions *optab, rtx target, rtx mem,
6587 rtx val, bool use_memmodel, enum memmodel model, bool after)
6588{
6589 machine_mode mode = GET_MODE (mem);
6590 struct expand_operand ops[4];
6591 enum insn_code icode;
6592 int op_counter = 0;
6593 int num_ops;
6594
6595 /* Check to see if there is a result returned. */
6596 if (target == const0_rtx)
6597 {
6598 if (use_memmodel)
6599 {
6600 icode = direct_optab_handler (optab->mem_no_result, mode);
6601 create_integer_operand (&ops[2], model);
6602 num_ops = 3;
6603 }
6604 else
6605 {
6606 icode = direct_optab_handler (optab->no_result, mode);
6607 num_ops = 2;
6608 }
6609 }
6610 /* Otherwise, we need to generate a result. */
6611 else
6612 {
6613 if (use_memmodel)
6614 {
6615 icode = direct_optab_handler (after ? optab->mem_fetch_after
6616 : optab->mem_fetch_before, mode);
6617 create_integer_operand (&ops[3], model);
6618 num_ops = 4;
6619 }
6620 else
6621 {
6622 icode = optab_handler (after ? optab->fetch_after
6623 : optab->fetch_before, mode);
6624 num_ops = 3;
6625 }
6626 create_output_operand (&ops[op_counter++], target, mode);
6627 }
6628 if (icode == CODE_FOR_nothing)
6629 return NULL_RTX;
6630
6631 create_fixed_operand (&ops[op_counter++], mem);
6632 /* VAL may have been promoted to a wider mode. Shrink it if so. */
6633 create_convert_operand_to (&ops[op_counter++], val, mode, true);
6634
6635 if (maybe_expand_insn (icode, num_ops, ops))
6636 return (target == const0_rtx ? const0_rtx : ops[0].value);
6637
6638 return NULL_RTX;
6639}
6640
6641
6642/* This function expands an atomic fetch_OP or OP_fetch operation:
6643 TARGET is an option place to stick the return value. const0_rtx indicates
6644 the result is unused.
6645 atomically fetch MEM, perform the operation with VAL and return it to MEM.
6646 CODE is the operation being performed (OP)
6647 MEMMODEL is the memory model variant to use.
6648 AFTER is true to return the result of the operation (OP_fetch).
6649 AFTER is false to return the value before the operation (fetch_OP).
6650
6651 This function will *only* generate instructions if there is a direct
6652 optab. No compare and swap loops or libcalls will be generated. */
6653
6654static rtx
6655expand_atomic_fetch_op_no_fallback (rtx target, rtx mem, rtx val,
6656 enum rtx_code code, enum memmodel model,
6657 bool after)
6658{
6659 machine_mode mode = GET_MODE (mem);
6660 struct atomic_op_functions optab;
6661 rtx result;
6662 bool unused_result = (target == const0_rtx);
6663
6664 get_atomic_op_for_code (&optab, code);
6665
6666 /* Check to see if there are any better instructions. */
6667 result = maybe_optimize_fetch_op (target, mem, val, code, model, after);
6668 if (result)
6669 return result;
6670
6671 /* Check for the case where the result isn't used and try those patterns. */
6672 if (unused_result)
6673 {
6674 /* Try the memory model variant first. */
6675 result = maybe_emit_op (&optab, target, mem, val, true, model, true);
6676 if (result)
6677 return result;
6678
6679 /* Next try the old style withuot a memory model. */
6680 result = maybe_emit_op (&optab, target, mem, val, false, model, true);
6681 if (result)
6682 return result;
6683
6684 /* There is no no-result pattern, so try patterns with a result. */
6685 target = NULL_RTX;
6686 }
6687
6688 /* Try the __atomic version. */
6689 result = maybe_emit_op (&optab, target, mem, val, true, model, after);
6690 if (result)
6691 return result;
6692
6693 /* Try the older __sync version. */
6694 result = maybe_emit_op (&optab, target, mem, val, false, model, after);
6695 if (result)
6696 return result;
6697
6698 /* If the fetch value can be calculated from the other variation of fetch,
6699 try that operation. */
6700 if (after || unused_result || optab.reverse_code != UNKNOWN)
6701 {
6702 /* Try the __atomic version, then the older __sync version. */
6703 result = maybe_emit_op (&optab, target, mem, val, true, model, !after);
6704 if (!result)
6705 result = maybe_emit_op (&optab, target, mem, val, false, model, !after);
6706
6707 if (result)
6708 {
6709 /* If the result isn't used, no need to do compensation code. */
6710 if (unused_result)
6711 return result;
6712
6713 /* Issue compensation code. Fetch_after == fetch_before OP val.
6714 Fetch_before == after REVERSE_OP val. */
6715 if (!after)
6716 code = optab.reverse_code;
6717 if (code == NOT)
6718 {
6719 result = expand_simple_binop (mode, AND, result, val, NULL_RTX,
6720 true, OPTAB_LIB_WIDEN);
6721 result = expand_simple_unop (mode, NOT, result, target, true);
6722 }
6723 else
6724 result = expand_simple_binop (mode, code, result, val, target,
6725 true, OPTAB_LIB_WIDEN);
6726 return result;
6727 }
6728 }
6729
6730 /* No direct opcode can be generated. */
6731 return NULL_RTX;
6732}
6733
6734
6735
6736/* This function expands an atomic fetch_OP or OP_fetch operation:
6737 TARGET is an option place to stick the return value. const0_rtx indicates
6738 the result is unused.
6739 atomically fetch MEM, perform the operation with VAL and return it to MEM.
6740 CODE is the operation being performed (OP)
6741 MEMMODEL is the memory model variant to use.
6742 AFTER is true to return the result of the operation (OP_fetch).
6743 AFTER is false to return the value before the operation (fetch_OP). */
6744rtx
6745expand_atomic_fetch_op (rtx target, rtx mem, rtx val, enum rtx_code code,
6746 enum memmodel model, bool after)
6747{
6748 machine_mode mode = GET_MODE (mem);
6749 rtx result;
6750 bool unused_result = (target == const0_rtx);
6751
6752 /* If loads are not atomic for the required size and we are not called to
6753 provide a __sync builtin, do not do anything so that we stay consistent
6754 with atomic loads of the same size. */
6755 if (!can_atomic_load_p (mode) && !is_mm_sync (model))
6756 return NULL_RTX;
6757
6758 result = expand_atomic_fetch_op_no_fallback (target, mem, val, code, model,
6759 after);
6760
6761 if (result)
6762 return result;
6763
6764 /* Add/sub can be implemented by doing the reverse operation with -(val). */
6765 if (code == PLUS || code == MINUS)
6766 {
6767 rtx tmp;
6768 enum rtx_code reverse = (code == PLUS ? MINUS : PLUS);
6769
6770 start_sequence ();
6771 tmp = expand_simple_unop (mode, NEG, val, NULL_RTX, true);
6772 result = expand_atomic_fetch_op_no_fallback (target, mem, tmp, reverse,
6773 model, after);
6774 if (result)
6775 {
6776 /* PLUS worked so emit the insns and return. */
6777 tmp = get_insns ();
6778 end_sequence ();
6779 emit_insn (tmp);
6780 return result;
6781 }
6782
6783 /* PLUS did not work, so throw away the negation code and continue. */
6784 end_sequence ();
6785 }
6786
6787 /* Try the __sync libcalls only if we can't do compare-and-swap inline. */
6788 if (!can_compare_and_swap_p (mode, false))
6789 {
6790 rtx libfunc;
6791 bool fixup = false;
6792 enum rtx_code orig_code = code;
6793 struct atomic_op_functions optab;
6794
6795 get_atomic_op_for_code (&optab, code);
6796 libfunc = optab_libfunc (after ? optab.fetch_after
6797 : optab.fetch_before, mode);
6798 if (libfunc == NULL
6799 && (after || unused_result || optab.reverse_code != UNKNOWN))
6800 {
6801 fixup = true;
6802 if (!after)
6803 code = optab.reverse_code;
6804 libfunc = optab_libfunc (after ? optab.fetch_before
6805 : optab.fetch_after, mode);
6806 }
6807 if (libfunc != NULL)
6808 {
6809 rtx addr = convert_memory_address (ptr_mode, XEXP (mem, 0));
6810 result = emit_library_call_value (libfunc, NULL, LCT_NORMAL, mode,
6811 2, addr, ptr_mode, val, mode);
6812
6813 if (!unused_result && fixup)
6814 result = expand_simple_binop (mode, code, result, val, target,
6815 true, OPTAB_LIB_WIDEN);
6816 return result;
6817 }
6818
6819 /* We need the original code for any further attempts. */
6820 code = orig_code;
6821 }
6822
6823 /* If nothing else has succeeded, default to a compare and swap loop. */
6824 if (can_compare_and_swap_p (mode, true))
6825 {
6826 rtx_insn *insn;
6827 rtx t0 = gen_reg_rtx (mode), t1;
6828
6829 start_sequence ();
6830
6831 /* If the result is used, get a register for it. */
6832 if (!unused_result)
6833 {
6834 if (!target || !register_operand (target, mode))
6835 target = gen_reg_rtx (mode);
6836 /* If fetch_before, copy the value now. */
6837 if (!after)
6838 emit_move_insn (target, t0);
6839 }
6840 else
6841 target = const0_rtx;
6842
6843 t1 = t0;
6844 if (code == NOT)
6845 {
6846 t1 = expand_simple_binop (mode, AND, t1, val, NULL_RTX,
6847 true, OPTAB_LIB_WIDEN);
6848 t1 = expand_simple_unop (mode, code, t1, NULL_RTX, true);
6849 }
6850 else
6851 t1 = expand_simple_binop (mode, code, t1, val, NULL_RTX, true,
6852 OPTAB_LIB_WIDEN);
6853
6854 /* For after, copy the value now. */
6855 if (!unused_result && after)
6856 emit_move_insn (target, t1);
6857 insn = get_insns ();
6858 end_sequence ();
6859
6860 if (t1 != NULL && expand_compare_and_swap_loop (mem, t0, t1, insn))
6861 return target;
6862 }
6863
6864 return NULL_RTX;
6865}

6867/* Return true if OPERAND is suitable for operand number OPNO of
6868 instruction ICODE. */
6869
6870bool
6871insn_operand_matches (enum insn_code icode, unsigned int opno, rtx operand)
6872{
6873 return (!insn_data[(int) icode].operand[opno].predicate
6874 || (insn_data[(int) icode].operand[opno].predicate
6875 (operand, insn_data[(int) icode].operand[opno].mode)));
6876}
6877
6878/* TARGET is a target of a multiword operation that we are going to
6879 implement as a series of word-mode operations. Return true if
6880 TARGET is suitable for this purpose. */
6881
6882bool
6883valid_multiword_target_p (rtx target)
6884{
6885 machine_mode mode;
6886 int i;
6887
6888 mode = GET_MODE (target);
6889 for (i = 0; i < GET_MODE_SIZE (mode); i += UNITS_PER_WORD)
6890 if (!validate_subreg (word_mode, mode, target, i))
6891 return false;
6892 return true;
6893}
6894
6895/* Like maybe_legitimize_operand, but do not change the code of the
6896 current rtx value. */
6897
6898static bool
6899maybe_legitimize_operand_same_code (enum insn_code icode, unsigned int opno,
6900 struct expand_operand *op)
6901{
6902 /* See if the operand matches in its current form. */
6903 if (insn_operand_matches (icode, opno, op->value))
6904 return true;
6905
6906 /* If the operand is a memory whose address has no side effects,
6907 try forcing the address into a non-virtual pseudo register.
6908 The check for side effects is important because copy_to_mode_reg
6909 cannot handle things like auto-modified addresses. */
6910 if (insn_data[(int) icode].operand[opno].allows_mem && MEM_P (op->value))
6911 {
6912 rtx addr, mem;
6913
6914 mem = op->value;
6915 addr = XEXP (mem, 0);
6916 if (!(REG_P (addr) && REGNO (addr) > LAST_VIRTUAL_REGISTER)
6917 && !side_effects_p (addr))
6918 {
6919 rtx_insn *last;
6920 machine_mode mode;
6921
6922 last = get_last_insn ();
6923 mode = get_address_mode (mem);
6924 mem = replace_equiv_address (mem, copy_to_mode_reg (mode, addr));
6925 if (insn_operand_matches (icode, opno, mem))
6926 {
6927 op->value = mem;
6928 return true;
6929 }
6930 delete_insns_since (last);
6931 }
6932 }
6933
6934 return false;
6935}
6936
6937/* Try to make OP match operand OPNO of instruction ICODE. Return true
6938 on success, storing the new operand value back in OP. */
6939
6940static bool
6941maybe_legitimize_operand (enum insn_code icode, unsigned int opno,
6942 struct expand_operand *op)
6943{
6944 machine_mode mode, imode;
6945 bool old_volatile_ok, result;
6946
6947 mode = op->mode;
6948 switch (op->type)
6949 {
6950 case EXPAND_FIXED:
6951 old_volatile_ok = volatile_ok;
6952 volatile_ok = true;
6953 result = maybe_legitimize_operand_same_code (icode, opno, op);
6954 volatile_ok = old_volatile_ok;
6955 return result;
6956
6957 case EXPAND_OUTPUT:
6958 gcc_assert (mode != VOIDmode);
6959 if (op->value
6960 && op->value != const0_rtx
6961 && GET_MODE (op->value) == mode
6962 && maybe_legitimize_operand_same_code (icode, opno, op))
6963 return true;
6964
6965 op->value = gen_reg_rtx (mode);
6966 break;
6967
6968 case EXPAND_INPUT:
6969 input:
6970 gcc_assert (mode != VOIDmode);
6971 gcc_assert (GET_MODE (op->value) == VOIDmode
6972 || GET_MODE (op->value) == mode);
6973 if (maybe_legitimize_operand_same_code (icode, opno, op))
6974 return true;
6975
6976 op->value = copy_to_mode_reg (mode, op->value);
6977 break;
6978
6979 case EXPAND_CONVERT_TO:
6980 gcc_assert (mode != VOIDmode);
6981 op->value = convert_to_mode (mode, op->value, op->unsigned_p);
6982 goto input;
6983
6984 case EXPAND_CONVERT_FROM:
6985 if (GET_MODE (op->value) != VOIDmode)
6986 mode = GET_MODE (op->value);
6987 else
6988 /* The caller must tell us what mode this value has. */
6989 gcc_assert (mode != VOIDmode);
6990
6991 imode = insn_data[(int) icode].operand[opno].mode;
6992 if (imode != VOIDmode && imode != mode)
6993 {
6994 op->value = convert_modes (imode, mode, op->value, op->unsigned_p);
6995 mode = imode;
6996 }
6997 goto input;
6998
6999 case EXPAND_ADDRESS:
7000 gcc_assert (mode != VOIDmode);
7001 op->value = convert_memory_address (mode, op->value);
7002 goto input;
7003
7004 case EXPAND_INTEGER:
7005 mode = insn_data[(int) icode].operand[opno].mode;
7006 if (mode != VOIDmode && const_int_operand (op->value, mode))
7007 goto input;
7008 break;
7009 }
7010 return insn_operand_matches (icode, opno, op->value);
7011}

7013/* Make OP describe an input operand that should have the same value
7014 as VALUE, after any mode conversion that the target might request.
7015 TYPE is the type of VALUE. */
7016
7017void
7018create_convert_operand_from_type (struct expand_operand *op,
7019 rtx value, tree type)
7020{
7021 create_convert_operand_from (op, value, TYPE_MODE (type),
7022 TYPE_UNSIGNED (type));
7023}

7025/* Try to make operands [OPS, OPS + NOPS) match operands [OPNO, OPNO + NOPS)
7026 of instruction ICODE. Return true on success, leaving the new operand
7027 values in the OPS themselves. Emit no code on failure. */
7028
7029bool
7030maybe_legitimize_operands (enum insn_code icode, unsigned int opno,
7031 unsigned int nops, struct expand_operand *ops)
7032{
7033 rtx_insn *last;
7034 unsigned int i;
7035
7036 last = get_last_insn ();
7037 for (i = 0; i < nops; i++)
7038 if (!maybe_legitimize_operand (icode, opno + i, &ops[i]))
7039 {
7040 delete_insns_since (last);
7041 return false;
7042 }
7043 return true;
7044}
7045
7046/* Try to generate instruction ICODE, using operands [OPS, OPS + NOPS)
7047 as its operands. Return the instruction pattern on success,
7048 and emit any necessary set-up code. Return null and emit no
7049 code on failure. */
7050
7051rtx_insn *
7052maybe_gen_insn (enum insn_code icode, unsigned int nops,
7053 struct expand_operand *ops)
7054{
7055 gcc_assert (nops == (unsigned int) insn_data[(int) icode].n_generator_args);
7056 if (!maybe_legitimize_operands (icode, 0, nops, ops))
7057 return NULL;
7058
7059 switch (nops)
7060 {
7061 case 1:
7062 return GEN_FCN (icode) (ops[0].value);
7063 case 2:
7064 return GEN_FCN (icode) (ops[0].value, ops[1].value);
7065 case 3:
7066 return GEN_FCN (icode) (ops[0].value, ops[1].value, ops[2].value);
7067 case 4:
7068 return GEN_FCN (icode) (ops[0].value, ops[1].value, ops[2].value,
7069 ops[3].value);
7070 case 5:
7071 return GEN_FCN (icode) (ops[0].value, ops[1].value, ops[2].value,
7072 ops[3].value, ops[4].value);
7073 case 6:
7074 return GEN_FCN (icode) (ops[0].value, ops[1].value, ops[2].value,
7075 ops[3].value, ops[4].value, ops[5].value);
7076 case 7:
7077 return GEN_FCN (icode) (ops[0].value, ops[1].value, ops[2].value,
7078 ops[3].value, ops[4].value, ops[5].value,
7079 ops[6].value);
7080 case 8:
7081 return GEN_FCN (icode) (ops[0].value, ops[1].value, ops[2].value,
7082 ops[3].value, ops[4].value, ops[5].value,
7083 ops[6].value, ops[7].value);
7084 case 9:
7085 return GEN_FCN (icode) (ops[0].value, ops[1].value, ops[2].value,
7086 ops[3].value, ops[4].value, ops[5].value,
7087 ops[6].value, ops[7].value, ops[8].value);
7088 }
7089 gcc_unreachable ();
7090}
7091
7092/* Try to emit instruction ICODE, using operands [OPS, OPS + NOPS)
7093 as its operands. Return true on success and emit no code on failure. */
7094
7095bool
7096maybe_expand_insn (enum insn_code icode, unsigned int nops,
7097 struct expand_operand *ops)
7098{
7099 rtx_insn *pat = maybe_gen_insn (icode, nops, ops);
7100 if (pat)
7101 {
7102 emit_insn (pat);
7103 return true;
7104 }
7105 return false;
7106}

7123/* Emit instruction ICODE, using operands [OPS, OPS + NOPS)
7124 as its operands. */
7125
7126void
7127expand_insn (enum insn_code icode, unsigned int nops,
7128 struct expand_operand *ops)
7129{
7130 if (!maybe_expand_insn (icode, nops, ops))
7131 gcc_unreachable ();
7132}

7136void
7137expand_jump_insn (enum insn_code icode, unsigned int nops,

7140 if (!maybe_expand_jump_insn (icode, nops, ops))
7141 gcc_unreachable ();
7142}
